                           <q xml:lang="en"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;" unicode="">Fol. 206rb:</span><span style="line-height: 115%;" unicode="">This (is) the book of &#704;Add Grat of the church of Cyricus and his mother Julitta.</span><span style="line-height: 115%;" unicode="">&#160;May the one who stole and who erased (it's text) be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul. The one who bought it with his money (is) d&#228;&#287;&#287;azma&#269; Kasa who is T&#228;sfa Maryam, so that it might be for him the salvation of (his) body and soul in the new Kingdom of Heaven along with his father Z&#228;-M&#228;nf&#228;s Q&#477;ddus and his mother &#704;Aqlisya, forever and ever. Amen.</span></span></q>
                           <p/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#"><span style="font-size: small">Fol. 206vab: Excerpt from a liturgical text (?).</span></locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;" unicode="">Fol. 206vab: Listen to our Lord, all you churches, for He is the one who glorified the &#704;Orit and the Prophets in the Gospel of the Kingdom saying, Kr&#477;stos son of David, &#8220;Amen&#8230;&#8221;</span></span></q>
                           <p/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><span style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt" unicode="">Fol. 206vb-207va: Prayer of the blessing, oh Triune Holy, Father, Son and Holy Spirit (give your) bless on your lovely Christian people&#8230; </span></q>
                           <p/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#00"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><span style="font-size: small;"><span unicode="" style="line-height: 115%;">Fols. 207vb-208rb: Psalm. He was crucified and suffered without sin, His ribs was pierced without pain because His divinity did not suffer&#8230;</span></span></q>
                           <p/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) added in the upper margins in fols. 115r, 123v, 124v, 125v, 131rv, 132r, 152v, 158rv, 159rv, 164r, 167rv, 173r.&#xD;
- The original name(s) mentioned in the supplication formulas has been erased throughout the Ms. (e.g., 11va l.15, 11vb l.16, 16ra l.24).&#xD;
- The title of the work is written by pen in fol. 1r.&#xD;
- Word kiralayson inserted interlineally, by the same hand as that of Additio 1: fol. 206ra.</item>
